info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Estimate the empiric distribution of a sample of measures contained in the array with n bins.

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- output measure type : not used.
- measure : input measure.
- bin number : number of equally spaced intervals in which the interval [min,max] will be subdivided,
               with min and max representing the minimum and the maximum values in the array.
- mode : type of requested output
         -- 'RANGES': get only interval ranges;
         -- 'FREQS': get only the values of each bin;
         -- 'ALL' : get ranges and frequencies (default).
                           In this case the format will be:
                           <range[0],bin[0],range[1],bin[1],â€¦,range[nbin-1],bin[nbin-1],range[nbin]>
- flag : type of returned frequencies
         -- 'ABS': get the absolute frequencies for each bin (default);
         -- 'PDF': get the normalized frequencies with respect to the total number of samples, that is the pdf;
         -- 'CDF': get the normalized and cumulative frequencies with respect to the total number of samples, that is the cdf.                        

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
Estimate the empiric distribution of a set of oph_double with 10 bins. Return ranges and absolute frequencies.
oph_gsl_histogram('OPH_DOUBLE','',measure,10)
